HEADWORD: Analysis of variance
<hw>A*nal"y*sis of variance</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Statistics)</fld> <def>a statistical technique by which the
results of an observation or experiment are analyzed to determine the
relative contributions of the different possible causative factors or
variables to the outcome. Abbreviated
<altname>ANOVA</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
